  "response_text": "Here's a healthy dinner idea that can serve a family of five:\n\n**Grilled Chicken Fajitas with Roasted Vegetables**\n\nIngredients:\n\n* 1 lb boneless, skinless chicken breast, cut into strips\n* 1 large onion, sliced\n* 2 large bell peppers (any color), sliced\n* 2 large zucchinis, sliced\n* 2 cloves of garlic, minced\n* 1 tablespoon olive oil\n* 1 teaspoon cumin\n* 1 teaspoon chili powder\n* Salt and pepper, to taste\n* 5 whole wheat tortillas\n* Optional toppings: avocado, sour cream, salsa, shredded cheese, cilantro\n\nInstructions:\n\n1. Preheat the grill to medium-high heat. Season the chicken with cumin, chili powder, salt, and pepper. Grill the chicken for 5-6 minutes per side, or until cooked through.\n2. In a large bowl, toss the sliced onion, bell peppers, and zucchinis with olive oil, garlic, salt, and pepper. Spread the vegetables on a baking sheet and roast in the oven at 400°F (200°C) for 20-25 minutes, or until tender.\n3. Warm the whole wheat tortillas by wrapping them in a damp paper towel and microwaving for 20-30 seconds.\n4. Assemble the fajitas by slicing the grilled chicken and adding it to the tortillas along with the roasted vegetables. Serve with your choice of toppings.\n\n**Side Dish: Mexican Street Corn**\n\n* 5 ears of corn, husked and silked\n* 2 tablespoons olive oil\n* 1 tablespoon lime juice\n* 1 teaspoon ground cumin\n* Salt and pepper, to taste\n* 1/4 cup crumbled queso fresco (or feta cheese)\n* Chopped cilantro, for garnish\n\nGrill the corn on the cob for 10-15 minutes, turning frequently, until lightly charred. Slather with olive oil, lime juice, and cumin. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with queso fresco and garnish with cilantro.\n\n**Beverage: Fresh Fruit Infused Water**\n\n* 1 pitcher of water\n* Slices of orange, lemon, lime, and cucumber\n* Fresh mint leaves\n\nAdd slices of citrus fruits and cucumber to a pitcher of water. Add a few sprigs of fresh mint leaves for a refreshing and healthy beverage.\n\nThis meal is not only delicious, but it's also packed with nutrients, fiber, and protein to keep your family satisfied and energized. Enjoy!",
